00:12:52,646 --> 00:12:54,064
It's cozy. Want to come up?

261
00:13:00,738 --> 00:13:02,656
Oh, I couldn't sleep up here.

262
00:13:02,740 --> 00:13:04,366
But I can.

263
00:13:18,422 --> 00:13:21,133
<i>What do I like about this guy?</i>

264
00:13:23,344 --> 00:13:25,429
<i>It was a brief moment. Like five minutes?</i>

265
00:13:25,513 --> 00:13:27,014
<i>We were very close to each other.</i>

266
00:13:27,097 --> 00:13:29,600
Because of that, I got butterflies
first thing in the morning.

267
00:13:30,184 --> 00:13:31,143
Over here is…

268
00:13:31,227 --> 00:13:34,438
<i>Since we stayed in the same house</i>
<i>for two days in a row,</i>

269
00:13:34,522 --> 00:13:36,941
<i>there was a level of comfort</i>
<i>that came from that.</i>

270
00:13:37,024 --> 00:13:39,693
-Where?
-Jun-seung is just a wallflower here.

271
00:13:39,777 --> 00:13:40,986
Oh, he's back there.

272
00:13:41,070 --> 00:13:42,154
He is back there.

273
00:13:42,238 --> 00:13:45,241
But they don't care
if Jun-seung is there or not.

274
00:13:46,617 --> 00:13:50,079
<i>Since we stayed in the same house</i>
<i>for two days in a row,</i>

275
00:13:50,162 --> 00:13:52,665
<i>there was a level of comfort</i>
<i>that came from that.</i>

276
00:13:52,748 --> 00:13:55,042
<i>Because I know how Hyun-jin feels,</i>

277
00:13:55,125 --> 00:13:58,212
<i>I should get to know Ji-young</i>
<i>without delay</i>

278
00:13:58,295 --> 00:14:00,130
so that I can give

279
00:14:00,214 --> 00:14:02,508
Hyun-jin a clear answer.

280
00:14:03,092 --> 00:14:04,009
I'll go chat with her.

281
00:14:06,679 --> 00:14:07,513
Take your time.

282
00:14:09,765 --> 00:14:11,684
<i>I'm sure he needs that opportunity.</i>

283
00:14:11,767 --> 00:14:12,768
<i>But the thing is,</i>

284
00:14:12,851 --> 00:14:15,187
I'm only thinking about whether things

285
00:14:15,271 --> 00:14:18,107
will work out with him, not anyone else.

286
00:14:18,607 --> 00:14:21,151
<i>I guess he can be</i>
<i>curious about the other person too.</i>

287
00:14:21,777 --> 00:14:22,611
<i>Sure.</i>

288
00:14:23,237 --> 00:14:24,071
<i>He should do it.</i>

289
00:14:25,698 --> 00:14:27,950
I'm going to chat with Ji-young today.

290
00:14:30,411 --> 00:14:31,871
I haven't spoken to her at all.

291
00:14:34,832 --> 00:14:36,584
If he was really cool about it,

292
00:14:36,667 --> 00:14:38,502
he would've said, "Sure."

293
00:14:38,586 --> 00:14:40,254
But he wants to act cool,
but he can't, so…

294
00:14:41,255 --> 00:14:43,048
-He can't even look at him
-He can't.

295
00:14:43,132 --> 00:14:44,925
since his feelings would show.

296
00:14:47,219 --> 00:14:51,015
<i>I thought I'd be okay about giving him</i>
<i>an opportunity until the second day,</i>

297
00:14:51,098 --> 00:14:53,601
but now, I don't think I really
want to give him that chance.

298
00:14:53,684 --> 00:14:55,019
Hello.

299
00:14:56,520 --> 00:14:57,688
Are you talking to me?

300
00:14:57,771 --> 00:14:59,189
-Who? Is it you?
-Yeah.

301
00:15:00,316 --> 00:15:02,568
-Hi. Did you sleep well?
-Of course.

302
00:15:02,651 --> 00:15:06,071
Let's have a chat once you're done.

303
00:15:06,780 --> 00:15:08,157
Okay, got it.

304
00:15:08,240 --> 00:15:10,367
<i>I think Jun-seung gave me a chance</i>

305
00:15:10,451 --> 00:15:12,077
<i>since I wanted to chat with Si-hyun.</i>

306
00:15:12,161 --> 00:15:15,039
<i>My feelings for Jun-seung aren't growing,</i>

307
00:15:15,122 --> 00:15:16,790
<i>but that doesn't mean</i>

308
00:15:16,874 --> 00:15:19,001
<i>I'm going all in with Si-hyun either.</i>

309
00:15:19,084 --> 00:15:20,753
Honestly, I'm on the verge of giving up.

310
00:15:20,836 --> 00:15:22,922
<i>As long as Hyun-jin is by his side,</i>

311
00:15:23,005 --> 00:15:25,841
<i>I don't think I'll stand a chance.</i>

312
00:15:25,925 --> 00:15:30,846
<i>I don't think I can turn things around</i>
<i>or anything like that.</i>

313
00:15:31,347 --> 00:15:34,141
At least, if I expressed how I felt,

314
00:15:34,224 --> 00:15:37,436
I wouldn't have any regrets
and feel light.

315
00:15:37,937 --> 00:15:40,314
-Is there anything you want to know?
-Anything I want to know?

316
00:15:40,397 --> 00:15:44,193
The thing is, you seem close

317
00:15:44,276 --> 00:15:47,905
with Hyun-jin
and you spend a lot of time together,

318
00:15:47,988 --> 00:15:50,407
so I feel like there's no room for me.

319
00:15:50,491 --> 00:15:53,786
-I see.
-So I thought I wouldn't get

320
00:15:53,869 --> 00:15:55,329
a chance to talk with you.

321
00:15:55,412 --> 00:15:57,414
That would be too disappointing.

322
00:15:57,498 --> 00:15:59,625
If we don't chat here,
we can't have a birthday party together.

323
00:16:01,210 --> 00:16:03,003
Although it's still far away.

324
00:16:03,087 --> 00:16:05,798
As soon as I saw the ideal type you wrote

325
00:16:05,881 --> 00:16:07,591
on your self-introduction letter,

326
00:16:07,675 --> 00:16:09,385
I immediately thought

327
00:16:10,010 --> 00:16:12,137
it wasn't me. It was Hyun-jin.

328
00:16:12,221 --> 00:16:14,348
-Really?
-Yeah, that's what I thought.

329
00:16:14,431 --> 00:16:16,016
-And besides the looks?
-Besides that?

330
00:16:16,100 --> 00:16:17,685
Besides that,

331
00:16:17,768 --> 00:16:20,562
I thought you and I would click.

332
00:16:20,646 --> 00:16:22,856
I'd think we'd click,

333
00:16:22,940 --> 00:16:24,733
but the ideal type held me back.

334
00:16:24,817 --> 00:16:26,568
In terms of looks, you mean?

335
00:16:27,236 --> 00:16:29,071
Yeah, I didn't think that was me.

336
00:16:29,780 --> 00:16:33,075
I don't think what I wrote
in the letter really matters.

337
00:16:33,158 --> 00:16:34,618
It's just an ideal type.

338
00:16:34,702 --> 00:16:37,454
All the women I met were
different from each other.

339
00:16:38,205 --> 00:16:40,958
It was such a shame
that we had such little time.

340
00:16:41,041 --> 00:16:42,960
Yeah, I agree.

341
00:16:46,171 --> 00:16:48,757
SOMETIME PAST NOON

342
00:16:55,055 --> 00:16:56,390
-Wait.
-What?

343
00:16:59,435 --> 00:17:02,479
"You can win a six-hour escape date pass."

344
00:17:04,440 --> 00:17:05,691
ISOLATED WITH THE IDEAL TYPE
DAY THREE

345
00:17:05,774 --> 00:17:06,817
THE NIGHTLY HEART CHIP VOTES

346
00:17:06,900 --> 00:17:09,445
THE SUBJECTS EXPRESSED
HOW THEY FELT FOR TWO DAYS

347
00:17:09,528 --> 00:17:12,322
"The person who received
the most Heart Chips…

348
00:17:15,325 --> 00:17:16,243
is Ahn Si-hyun."

349
00:17:17,036 --> 00:17:17,870
CURRENT 1ST PLACE AHN SI-HYUN

350
00:17:17,953 --> 00:17:18,787
WEE JUN-SEUNG, 11 CHIPS

351
00:17:18,871 --> 00:17:19,872
LAH HYUN-JIN, 19 CHIPS

352
00:17:19,955 --> 00:17:20,789
BYEON JI-YOUNG, 119 CHIPS

353
00:17:20,873 --> 00:17:22,124
AHN SI-HYUN, 120 CHIPS

354
00:17:22,207 --> 00:17:24,460
TOTAL COUNT OF HEART CHIPS
1ST PLACE: AHN SI-HYUN, 120 CHIPS

355
00:17:24,543 --> 00:17:28,797
"Designate one person to go
on the date with and leave immediately."

356
00:17:28,881 --> 00:17:30,716
THE CHOICE IS UP TO SI-HYUN

357
00:17:34,970 --> 00:17:35,804
Six hours?

358
00:17:35,888 --> 00:17:37,389
<i>I thought he'd go with Hyun-jin.</i>

359
00:17:37,473 --> 00:17:38,974
<i>I want to eat something good.</i>

360
00:17:42,186 --> 00:17:43,228
Let's go, Ji-young.

361
00:17:44,313 --> 00:17:45,147
Okay.

362
00:17:48,442 --> 00:17:49,526
Oh my.

363
00:17:50,778 --> 00:17:51,779
Oh my goodness.

364
00:17:52,321 --> 00:17:53,655
You know,

365
00:17:53,739 --> 00:17:56,533
whenever the men win something,
they choose Ji-young.

366
00:17:57,201 --> 00:17:59,328
She went on the convenience store date.

367
00:17:59,411 --> 00:18:02,581
I bet Hyun-jin really wants to
get out of there.

368
00:18:03,999 --> 00:18:05,000
Let's go, Ji-young.

369
00:18:06,085 --> 00:18:06,919
Okay.

370
00:18:10,380 --> 00:18:11,965
<i>It was totally unexpected.</i>

371
00:18:12,049 --> 00:18:16,553
<i>When he said he was going to</i>
<i>create an opportunity in the note,</i>

372
00:18:16,637 --> 00:18:20,599
I thought he meant
he'd pull me aside for a quick chat.

373
00:18:20,682 --> 00:18:25,938
But he chose me for the seemingly
important six-hour escape date pass.

374
00:18:26,563 --> 00:18:28,440
I didn't expect that at all.

375
00:18:28,941 --> 00:18:31,151
Whether it was outside or in here,

376
00:18:31,235 --> 00:18:34,446
it was a chance for me
to have a chat with Ji-young.

377
00:18:34,530 --> 00:18:36,031
That's all I was thinking.

378
00:18:36,115 --> 00:18:37,866
See you, guys.

379
00:18:37,950 --> 00:18:39,743
Isn't this more special?

380
00:18:42,496 --> 00:18:44,456
Isn't this better than chopping wood?

381
00:18:44,540 --> 00:18:45,415
Don't cry.

382
00:18:45,499 --> 00:18:46,917
You should complain to them.

383
00:18:47,501 --> 00:18:48,752
I object.

384
00:18:50,838 --> 00:18:52,631
I think I felt a little jealous.

385
00:18:53,215 --> 00:18:54,800
<i>So he got the most chips.</i>

386
00:18:55,592 --> 00:18:58,720
<i>I was the one who made it possible</i>
<i>for them to go on a date.</i>

387
00:18:58,804 --> 00:19:00,013
<i>But he said he wanted to</i>

388
00:19:00,597 --> 00:19:02,933
<i>get to know Ji-young</i>
<i>since he hadn't gotten a chance.</i>

389
00:19:03,934 --> 00:19:05,561
<i>Then, go right ahead.</i>

390
00:19:05,644 --> 00:19:07,771
If the choice was up to me,

391
00:19:07,855 --> 00:19:09,565
I would have gone with Si-hyun.

392
00:19:09,648 --> 00:19:11,441
See you.

393
00:19:11,525 --> 00:19:12,401
See you.

394
00:19:12,943 --> 00:19:14,570
Let's eat the curry later.

395
00:19:14,653 --> 00:19:15,571
For dinner.

396
00:19:16,155 --> 00:19:17,072
What are you going to wear?

397
00:19:17,156 --> 00:19:17,990
Pick it out for me.

398
00:19:18,073 --> 00:19:19,158
-How about this one?
-This one?

399
00:19:19,241 --> 00:19:20,200
I'm wearing a gray cardigan.

400
00:19:20,284 --> 00:19:21,702
Really? Okay.

401
00:19:21,785 --> 00:19:22,786
Let's go with gray.

402
00:19:23,370 --> 00:19:24,204
Gray.

403
00:19:24,288 --> 00:19:25,873
<i>I was a bit worried as well.</i>

404
00:19:25,956 --> 00:19:27,791
Since we hadn't had
a real conversation yet,

405
00:19:27,875 --> 00:19:29,585
I hoped we could click.

406
00:19:29,668 --> 00:19:32,254
I was happy, for sure.

407
00:19:32,337 --> 00:19:36,091
But there were some concerns
that came with that too.

408
00:19:36,175 --> 00:19:38,969
-I don't feel completely at ease.
-Why?

409
00:19:39,052 --> 00:19:40,596
Hyun-jin keeps

410
00:19:41,305 --> 00:19:42,181
weighing on my mind.

411
00:19:42,264 --> 00:19:44,308
I'm not concerned about that at all.

412
00:19:44,391 --> 00:19:45,392
Really? I don't know.

413
00:19:45,976 --> 00:19:47,811
-I try not to--
-Love is a battle.

414
00:19:48,312 --> 00:19:50,689
Well, I'm not good at things like that.

415
00:19:51,315 --> 00:19:52,774
I wasn't good at that out there either.

416
00:19:53,734 --> 00:19:55,402
I got things taken away
from me all the time.

417
00:19:56,612 --> 00:19:58,530
"Taken away." That's sad.

418
00:19:59,156 --> 00:20:01,200
Because I need to get the things I want.

419
00:20:03,368 --> 00:20:06,580
You couldn't do it out there,
but you can do it here.

420
00:20:07,623 --> 00:20:08,498
I'll give it a shot.

421
00:20:12,461 --> 00:20:14,421
-What's up?
-May I get by?

422
00:20:29,645 --> 00:20:30,604
Are you grabbing a bite?

423
00:20:31,230 --> 00:20:32,231
No.

424
00:20:37,069 --> 00:20:38,570
-What are you doing?
-It's a secret.

425
00:20:44,034 --> 00:20:45,577
<i>I tried to look away from them.</i>

426
00:20:45,661 --> 00:20:49,706
It's not that I find it unpleasant.
But I felt like I didn't have to see them.

427
00:20:51,959 --> 00:20:53,043
Are they leaving now?

428
00:20:53,126 --> 00:20:56,588
<i>Jun-seung acted like he didn't care,</i>
<i>but his attention was totally on them.</i>

429
00:20:57,214 --> 00:20:59,466
-Go check them out if you're curious.
-I don't want to.

430
00:21:00,217 --> 00:21:01,301
-No?
-Why would I?

431
00:21:02,094 --> 00:21:02,928
SI-HYUN AND JI-YOUNG PASS THE CAFE

432
00:21:03,011 --> 00:21:04,471
It's so close.

433
00:21:11,061 --> 00:21:14,356
They said it was a special date yesterday,
but it was at a convenience store.

434
00:21:14,439 --> 00:21:16,358
So I wonder what it'll be like

435
00:21:16,984 --> 00:21:17,818
this time.

436
00:21:17,901 --> 00:21:19,736
-It'll be really special.
-Yeah.

437
00:21:19,820 --> 00:21:20,988
It's the last one.

438
00:21:21,071 --> 00:21:22,948
It feels cooler down here.

439
00:21:23,031 --> 00:21:24,283
Yeah, it feels cool here.

440
00:21:24,366 --> 00:21:26,285
-I was here yesterday too.
-Yeah.

441
00:21:26,368 --> 00:21:27,536
That's right.

442
00:21:27,619 --> 00:21:29,204
-You're so busy.
-Yesterday?

443
00:21:29,288 --> 00:21:31,915
It was a lot of walking up and down.

444
00:21:31,999 --> 00:21:34,584
Can you do long-distance
with someone in Changwon?

445
00:21:35,335 --> 00:21:36,962
We talked about that

446
00:21:37,045 --> 00:21:39,089
when we were in the Attic House.

447
00:21:39,172 --> 00:21:41,717
-It's much farther than I thought.
-Yeah.

448
00:21:41,800 --> 00:21:44,678
I've never been in a relationship
with someone that far away.

449
00:21:45,262 --> 00:21:46,346
Gosh.

450
00:21:46,430 --> 00:21:47,347
What is it?

451
00:21:47,431 --> 00:21:50,017
She told Jun-seung that
she likes long-distance relationships.

452
00:21:50,100 --> 00:21:50,934
That's right.

453
00:21:51,018 --> 00:21:52,477
She said she prefers it.

454
00:21:52,561 --> 00:21:54,813
That's right.
That way, she can have her own time.

455
00:21:54,896 --> 00:21:56,648
It's human instinct

456
00:21:56,732 --> 00:21:58,442
-To impress someone?
-to adjust to that person

457
00:21:58,525 --> 00:22:00,569
to impress them.

458
00:22:00,652 --> 00:22:04,156
-It's far.
-Let's say you really like this person.

459
00:22:04,239 --> 00:22:06,158
But they live that far.

460
00:22:06,241 --> 00:22:07,242
Would it still not work?

461
00:22:07,326 --> 00:22:10,454
If he really looks like my ideal type

462
00:22:10,537 --> 00:22:12,289
and I don't want to lose him,

463
00:22:12,372 --> 00:22:15,125
I could do long-distance then.

464
00:22:15,208 --> 00:22:16,418
-Really?
-Yeah.

465
00:22:16,501 --> 00:22:17,919
For a once-in-a-millennium
ideal type.

466
00:22:18,003 --> 00:22:20,255
-The edge-of-tofu?
-Yeah.

467
00:22:20,339 --> 00:22:23,300
Since I know my own ideal type,

468
00:22:23,383 --> 00:22:25,677
I'd like to go out with someone like that.

469
00:22:26,470 --> 00:22:28,180
<i>Gosh, I'm so happy.</i>

470
00:22:28,263 --> 00:22:29,389
<i>-We get to break away.</i>
<i>-Yeah.</i>

471
00:22:29,473 --> 00:22:31,308
<i>We're escaping the isolation.</i>

472
00:22:31,391 --> 00:22:33,977
I'm glad I was bad
at chopping wood yesterday.

473
00:22:35,604 --> 00:22:37,314
Is there anything you're curious about?

474
00:22:37,397 --> 00:22:38,231
There's a lot.

475
00:22:38,315 --> 00:22:39,775
How was it last night

476
00:22:39,858 --> 00:22:41,860
at the Attic House?

477
00:22:41,943 --> 00:22:44,529
-Jun-seung and I have been there, right?
-Yeah.

478
00:22:44,613 --> 00:22:46,239
We talked a lot about things like

479
00:22:46,323 --> 00:22:48,200
what we're like
when we're in a relationship,

480
00:22:48,283 --> 00:22:49,409
long-distance relationships…

481
00:22:49,493 --> 00:22:53,413
Have you talked a lot
about dating with Hyun-jin?

482
00:22:53,497 --> 00:22:55,207
No, not at all.

483
00:22:55,290 --> 00:22:56,500
What did you talk about then?

484
00:22:56,583 --> 00:22:58,418
-About life…
-You guys talk so much.

485
00:22:58,502 --> 00:23:00,295
-We talked about life.
-About life?

486
00:23:00,378 --> 00:23:02,047
We did talk about dating.

487
00:23:02,714 --> 00:23:03,673
That's right.

488
00:23:04,674 --> 00:23:08,595
Jun-seung only has eyes for you, right?

489
00:23:08,678 --> 00:23:09,805
How do you feel about that?

490
00:23:10,305 --> 00:23:12,891
-I'm so grateful for it. Yeah.
-Yeah.

491
00:23:12,974 --> 00:23:14,518
He's fun to be around.

492
00:23:14,601 --> 00:23:17,437
He's just very funny.

493
00:23:18,021 --> 00:23:20,273
I felt a bit disappointed

494
00:23:20,357 --> 00:23:22,484
when Jun-seung took you
to the convenience store.

495
00:23:22,567 --> 00:23:23,652
Why?

496
00:23:23,735 --> 00:23:27,030
That was a chance for me
to have a conversation with you.

497
00:23:27,114 --> 00:23:29,574
But Jun-seung isn't that forward…

498
00:23:30,200 --> 00:23:31,201
Or is he?

499
00:23:31,284 --> 00:23:33,370
I don't think he is <i>that</i> forward.

500
00:23:33,954 --> 00:23:35,789
-What?
-How forward does he have to be?

501
00:23:35,872 --> 00:23:38,208
-Should he pour 200 chips in?
-That's how she feels?

502
00:23:38,291 --> 00:23:39,417
Should he kiss her?

503
00:23:41,545 --> 00:23:44,047
Didn't he do everything but kiss her?

504
00:23:44,131 --> 00:23:46,633
-Gosh.
-I think they're both into each other.

505
00:23:46,716 --> 00:23:48,677
That's why they keep talking like that.

506
00:23:48,760 --> 00:23:50,470
They're finally talking freely.

507
00:23:51,304 --> 00:23:53,140
I wonder what will happen this evening.

508
00:23:54,474 --> 00:23:56,059
Are you wondering what they're doing?

509
00:23:56,643 --> 00:23:57,477
No.

510
00:23:58,228 --> 00:23:59,437
I'm not thinking about them.

511
00:24:01,773 --> 00:24:04,067
I think I wanted to know

512
00:24:04,151 --> 00:24:06,778
how certain he felt

513
00:24:06,862 --> 00:24:09,197
about Hyun-jin.

514
00:24:09,281 --> 00:24:11,741
I was curious about that.

515
00:24:12,617 --> 00:24:13,535
Are you curious?

516
00:24:14,703 --> 00:24:15,537
No.

517
00:24:16,830 --> 00:24:18,707
-I think you are.
-No, I'm not.

518
00:24:19,916 --> 00:24:22,169
HYUN-JIN AND JUN-SEUNG
ISOLATED HOUSE

519
00:24:24,212 --> 00:24:25,297
Where are you going?

520
00:24:26,006 --> 00:24:28,592
-A tree and a house, like this?
-Yeah.

521
00:24:28,675 --> 00:24:30,719
You're really good at this.

522
00:24:30,802 --> 00:24:31,845
I like how it looks.

523
00:24:32,429 --> 00:24:33,263
"It house"?

524
00:24:34,431 --> 00:24:35,432
It's a bear.

525
00:24:35,515 --> 00:24:36,474
It's a bus.

526
00:24:36,558 --> 00:24:37,475
That's a bear.

527
00:24:37,559 --> 00:24:39,102
Here's the mountain.

528
00:24:39,728 --> 00:24:40,896
The mountain.

529
00:24:40,979 --> 00:24:43,607
-You look like an artist.
-"It's me, perilla oil."

530
00:24:43,690 --> 00:24:45,567
I put too much pressure.

531
00:24:46,234 --> 00:24:47,652
You must be very stressed.

532
00:24:47,736 --> 00:24:49,446
-I couldn't control the pressure.
-You couldn't.

533
00:24:49,529 --> 00:24:50,572
I can't control the pressure.

534
00:24:52,574 --> 00:24:54,367
-Hey.
-Bobby!

535
00:25:01,374 --> 00:25:04,044
<i>The two of us had fun.</i>

536
00:25:04,127 --> 00:25:05,295
ISOLATION

537
00:25:05,378 --> 00:25:07,130
<i>-We did it.</i>
<i>-That was tough.</i>

538
00:25:07,923 --> 00:25:08,798
It's the first time

539
00:25:09,674 --> 00:25:11,259
-just being the two of us.
-Yeah.

540
00:25:11,343 --> 00:25:12,886
I was too…

541
00:25:12,969 --> 00:25:14,387
You were a bulldozer.

542
00:25:14,471 --> 00:25:15,639
I'm like a bulldozer.

543
00:25:15,722 --> 00:25:17,098
I'm not usually like this.

544
00:25:17,933 --> 00:25:19,643
But I thought I'd give it a try here

545
00:25:19,726 --> 00:25:21,061
if I fall for someone.

546
00:25:21,144 --> 00:25:22,145
What are you usually like?

547
00:25:22,229 --> 00:25:24,231
I usually don't express how I feel.

548
00:25:24,314 --> 00:25:25,899
I do when I'm seeing someone,

549
00:25:25,982 --> 00:25:27,108
but before that…

550
00:25:27,192 --> 00:25:28,526
But you were good at it.

551
00:25:28,610 --> 00:25:30,320
Well, I just did it.

552
00:25:31,112 --> 00:25:33,490
I didn't feel the need to play games.

553
00:25:33,573 --> 00:25:36,618
If it doesn't work out despite my efforts,
then so be it.

554
00:25:37,369 --> 00:25:38,245
That's cool.

555
00:25:39,329 --> 00:25:40,163
Thanks.

556
00:25:40,247 --> 00:25:41,748
-What about Si-hyun?
-Si-hyun?

557
00:25:42,874 --> 00:25:44,876
From what I can tell,

558
00:25:44,960 --> 00:25:46,586
he is pretty cautious as well.

559
00:25:47,087 --> 00:25:47,963
Yeah.

560
00:25:48,588 --> 00:25:50,215
It isn't easy to be like you.

561
00:25:50,298 --> 00:25:51,675
You're doing something difficult.

562
00:25:51,758 --> 00:25:53,301
It's my first time as well.

563
00:25:53,385 --> 00:25:55,178
I feel like I've lost control.

564
00:25:55,262 --> 00:25:56,346
I think so.

565
00:25:57,889 --> 00:25:59,933
I mean it's good.

566
00:26:00,016 --> 00:26:02,018
What do you think she's thinking?

567
00:26:02,102 --> 00:26:02,936
What she's thinking?

568
00:26:03,019 --> 00:26:05,897
Honestly, I don't know
what she's thinking.

569
00:26:06,564 --> 00:26:08,024
It's such a short time.

570
00:26:08,108 --> 00:26:10,110
-Not much could be done.
-I think so.

571
00:26:10,193 --> 00:26:14,531
Everyone is being cautious.
I'm the only one who seems frivolous.

572
00:26:14,614 --> 00:26:15,532
No.

573
00:26:15,615 --> 00:26:16,658
It could be the opposite.

574
00:26:16,741 --> 00:26:18,618
You could be the most serious.

575
00:26:19,995 --> 00:26:21,788
You're so serious. So damn serious.

576
00:26:21,871 --> 00:26:23,498
I should loosen up then.

577
00:26:23,581 --> 00:26:25,500
No, I think it's good.

578
00:26:25,583 --> 00:26:26,626
Is it?

579
00:26:27,252 --> 00:26:31,006
Is Si-hyun exactly the person
you're looking for?

580
00:26:31,089 --> 00:26:33,174
I'm torn.

581
00:26:33,258 --> 00:26:36,720
I think he is someone
I could end up liking.

582
00:26:36,803 --> 00:26:38,888
-I like him.
-But you're still unsure?

583
00:26:38,972 --> 00:26:40,807
You must be <i>really</i> torn then.

584
00:26:40,890 --> 00:26:43,601
-Yeah, I don't think I can change that.
-Sounds tough.

585
00:26:43,685 --> 00:26:45,312
What is your dilemma?

586
00:26:45,395 --> 00:26:47,022
Is it a matter of "Yes or no"

587
00:26:47,814 --> 00:26:48,648
or someone else?

588
00:26:48,732 --> 00:26:50,442
-I'm sure it's "Yes or no."
-Yeah.

589
00:26:55,447 --> 00:26:58,366
I was worried about you, though.

590
00:26:58,450 --> 00:26:59,701
Me? Why?

591
00:26:59,784 --> 00:27:01,661
I was worried you might feel hurt.

592
00:27:01,745 --> 00:27:02,579
About what?

593
00:27:02,662 --> 00:27:05,081
Because I only had eyes for her
which could have felt harsh.

594
00:27:06,750 --> 00:27:07,709
It's okay.

595
00:27:07,792 --> 00:27:09,044
You didn't feel hurt--

596
00:27:09,127 --> 00:27:10,337
I got over it.

597
00:27:10,420 --> 00:27:12,213
You got over it? So you <i>were</i> hurt?

598
00:27:12,297 --> 00:27:13,423
Of course not.

599
00:27:13,506 --> 00:27:14,716
Oh, okay. Got it.

600
00:27:17,302 --> 00:27:19,262
Even the subtitles are funny.

601
00:27:19,346 --> 00:27:20,930
It was funny how the music even stopped.

602
00:27:21,014 --> 00:27:22,807
Can you get that close in just three days?

603
00:27:22,891 --> 00:27:24,809
I'm like this with my decade-long friends.

604
00:27:24,893 --> 00:27:26,186
You know what would be interesting?

605
00:27:26,269 --> 00:27:28,271
Them ending up together after this show.

606
00:27:28,355 --> 00:27:30,398
-He was her ideal type at first.
-Exactly.

607
00:27:30,982 --> 00:27:33,109
Then, it would be so darn fun.

608
00:27:33,193 --> 00:27:34,861
You seem very comfortable with me.

609
00:27:34,944 --> 00:27:37,405
I like you so much.

610
00:27:37,489 --> 00:27:38,823
I think you are

611
00:27:38,907 --> 00:27:40,325
so funny.

612
00:27:40,408 --> 00:27:41,743
Since yesterday,

613
00:27:42,410 --> 00:27:43,578
you've become a different person.

614
00:27:47,707 --> 00:27:50,210
JI-YOUNG AND SI-HYUN
LA MAISON DE MARIE

615
00:27:50,960 --> 00:27:52,670
You have the cherry blossom view.

616
00:27:52,754 --> 00:27:54,506
<i>Yeah, totally a cherry blossom view.</i>

617
00:27:56,049 --> 00:27:58,009
-And I have the duck view.
-What?

618
00:27:58,510 --> 00:28:00,595
-Think of it as "Ji-young view."
-"Ji-young view"?

619
00:28:00,678 --> 00:28:01,763
-Yeah.
-I like that.

620
00:28:01,846 --> 00:28:03,348
-Ji-young view.
-Ji-young view.

621
00:28:03,431 --> 00:28:04,682
Ji-young view.

622
00:28:04,766 --> 00:28:05,809
-Ji-young view?
-Ji-young view.

623
00:28:07,060 --> 00:28:08,186
<i>How adorable.</i>

624
00:28:08,269 --> 00:28:09,729
<i>They must have</i>

625
00:28:10,730 --> 00:28:12,482
-ice cream as well.
-How cute.

626
00:28:14,067 --> 00:28:15,402
-Let's share.
-Okay.

627
00:28:15,485 --> 00:28:17,112
-Why didn't you get coffee?
-What?

628
00:28:17,195 --> 00:28:19,739
You were debating
between the strawberry and this.

629
00:28:19,823 --> 00:28:21,241
So I can try both?

630
00:28:21,324 --> 00:28:23,034
Yeah, you were debating between the two.

631
00:28:23,118 --> 00:28:23,952
EARLIER

632
00:28:24,035 --> 00:28:25,787
Should I have strawberry or matcha?

633
00:28:25,870 --> 00:28:26,704
I'll do matcha latte.

634
00:28:26,788 --> 00:28:27,997
-Matcha latte?
-Yeah.

635
00:28:28,081 --> 00:28:30,166
-Then, I'll get the strawberry latte.
-Really?

636
00:28:31,793 --> 00:28:33,795
I love it when someone does that.

637
00:28:33,878 --> 00:28:35,380
When I can't decide between two options,

638
00:28:35,463 --> 00:28:37,006
he goes, "Then, I'll get the matcha."

639
00:28:37,090 --> 00:28:38,216
So that I can try it.

640
00:28:38,299 --> 00:28:41,177
You tell me to just get what you want.

641
00:28:42,303 --> 00:28:43,847
What a charmer!

642
00:28:43,930 --> 00:28:46,641
It's been so long
since I got a proper dessert like this.

643
00:28:46,725 --> 00:28:48,518
-For real.
-Right?

644
00:28:52,480 --> 00:28:54,315
It feels like a real date.

645
00:28:54,399 --> 00:28:55,233
Right?

646
00:28:57,819 --> 00:28:58,820
That's what matters.

647
00:29:01,030 --> 00:29:01,865
There.

648
00:29:02,866 --> 00:29:05,493
IT'S NOISY OUTSIDE BECAUSE OF THE CHILDREN

649
00:29:05,577 --> 00:29:06,411
So cute.

650
00:29:07,412 --> 00:29:09,122
-Do you like children?
-I love them.

651
00:29:09,205 --> 00:29:12,041
-Remember I said I want to get married?
-Yeah.

652
00:29:12,125 --> 00:29:14,043
It's because I want to have kids.

653
00:29:14,127 --> 00:29:16,379
Just like what my parents did for me,

654
00:29:16,463 --> 00:29:17,964
I'd like to have

655
00:29:18,047 --> 00:29:20,467
the ability to let my children
pursue what they want to do.

656
00:29:20,550 --> 00:29:22,719
-I see.
-My idea of success

657
00:29:22,802 --> 00:29:24,721
is having the ability to do that.

658
00:29:24,804 --> 00:29:27,265
That's how I'm living my life,

659
00:29:27,348 --> 00:29:29,809
and that's why I want to get married.

660
00:29:29,893 --> 00:29:33,980
The reason why I want to get married
is because I want children.

661
00:29:34,063 --> 00:29:37,817
Even though I have this thought,

662
00:29:37,901 --> 00:29:40,570
-if the other person doesn't want it,
-If they don't want it…

663
00:29:40,653 --> 00:29:42,113
you can't do it.

664
00:29:42,197 --> 00:29:44,282
So it's important for me to find someone

665
00:29:44,365 --> 00:29:46,326
who agrees with me on things like that.

666
00:29:46,409 --> 00:29:48,953
That's why when it comes to dating,

667
00:29:49,579 --> 00:29:51,539
it can't just be about feelings.

668
00:29:51,623 --> 00:29:52,957
I see.

669
00:29:53,917 --> 00:29:56,044
I want to get married fast too,

670
00:29:56,127 --> 00:29:59,255
and it's been my dream
to start a stable family of my own.

671
00:29:59,339 --> 00:30:02,759
When I heard what he said,
I realized we agreed on that.

672
00:30:02,842 --> 00:30:08,056
I felt like our values about marriage
are well-aligned.

673
00:30:08,139 --> 00:30:11,351
On one hand, I thought we were
very well-aligned,

674
00:30:11,434 --> 00:30:13,686
but I was wondering
if she was just going along with me.

675
00:30:13,770 --> 00:30:16,314
She said she can adjust herself
to the other person

676
00:30:16,397 --> 00:30:22,237
and if she likes someone,
she's willing to do anything for them.

677
00:30:22,320 --> 00:30:25,073
Yeah, I want to adjust to my guy
since I like him.

678
00:30:25,156 --> 00:30:26,908
You tend to adjust yourself to match him.

679
00:30:26,991 --> 00:30:28,576
Yeah, I'd like to do that.

680
00:30:28,660 --> 00:30:31,120
I'd like to adjust to him
since I like him.

681
00:30:31,704 --> 00:30:34,123
If you were to accommodate him
in every aspect,

682
00:30:34,207 --> 00:30:35,667
you'll end up feeling drained.

683
00:30:36,167 --> 00:30:37,335
Yeah.

684
00:30:37,418 --> 00:30:42,173
<i>I was wondering if she was</i>
<i>just telling me what I wanted to hear.</i>

685
00:30:42,882 --> 00:30:43,716
MUSIC PLAYS SUDDENLY

686
00:30:43,800 --> 00:30:44,926
Is it closing time?

687
00:30:45,426 --> 00:30:46,970
"Thank you for your hard work today."

688
00:30:47,053 --> 00:30:48,263
"Goodbye."

689
00:30:48,346 --> 00:30:49,639
"See you again."

690
00:30:51,307 --> 00:30:53,268
You really go along with everything I do.

691
00:30:53,351 --> 00:30:54,435
That's who I am.

692
00:30:54,519 --> 00:30:55,854
<i>That's who I am</i>

693
00:30:58,064 --> 00:30:58,940
I'm having fun.

694
00:31:00,775 --> 00:31:01,651
Me too.

695
00:31:02,652 --> 00:31:04,028
-Too late.
-Sorry.

696
00:31:05,113 --> 00:31:06,656
Can you give me one more chance?

697
00:31:06,739 --> 00:31:07,657
-I'm having fun.
-Yeah.

698
00:31:11,828 --> 00:31:13,288
We have a similar sense of humor.

699
00:31:13,371 --> 00:31:14,789
I know.

700
00:31:16,332 --> 00:31:17,333
-What?
-They click well.

701
00:31:17,417 --> 00:31:18,501
They really click.

702
00:31:18,585 --> 00:31:20,336
That exchange gave me butterflies.

703
00:31:20,420 --> 00:31:22,338
Si-hyun and Hyun-jin didn't have
that kind of chemistry.

704
00:31:22,422 --> 00:31:24,257
They didn't have that giggling chemistry.

705
00:31:24,340 --> 00:31:26,551
And neither did Jun-seung and Ji-young.

706
00:31:26,634 --> 00:31:28,928
-They keep joking around with each other.
-Yeah.

707
00:31:29,012 --> 00:31:31,264
You need to have
a similar sense of humor.

708
00:31:31,347 --> 00:31:36,561
Our conversations flowed easily,
like casual small talk.

709
00:31:36,644 --> 00:31:39,981
I actually prefer conversations like that.

710
00:31:40,064 --> 00:31:43,818
It was like talking to a friend,
but I still got butterflies.

711
00:31:43,902 --> 00:31:46,571
When I chatted with Hyun-jin,

712
00:31:46,654 --> 00:31:48,072
it was fun and all,

713
00:31:48,156 --> 00:31:50,241
but I didn't feel completely at ease.

714
00:31:50,325 --> 00:31:51,993
But when I was chatting with Ji-young,

715
00:31:52,076 --> 00:31:54,412
I found myself at ease.

716
00:31:54,495 --> 00:31:57,665
We exchanged a lot of funny jokes as well.

717
00:31:57,749 --> 00:31:59,584
Now that we finally got to chat--

718
00:31:59,667 --> 00:32:01,377
-You feel at ease, right?
-Yes.

719
00:32:01,461 --> 00:32:03,296
It changed completely.

720
00:32:04,339 --> 00:32:06,716
It's because we're by ourselves,

721
00:32:06,799 --> 00:32:09,802
away from the people
that might weigh on our minds.

722
00:32:09,886 --> 00:32:12,847
You said Hyun-jin was
on your mind earlier.

723
00:32:12,931 --> 00:32:13,973
Do you still feel that way?

724
00:32:15,183 --> 00:32:16,434
I don't think so.

725
00:32:16,517 --> 00:32:18,770
As we talked, I forgot about her.

726
00:32:19,687 --> 00:32:20,563
Then…

727
00:32:22,357 --> 00:32:23,191
Jun-seung?

728
00:32:24,901 --> 00:32:27,153
I'm not really thinking about him much.

729
00:32:30,406 --> 00:32:31,532
Shall I play the guitar?

730
00:32:35,203 --> 00:32:36,621
Nice vibes.

731
00:32:37,205 --> 00:32:38,081
Like an "it guy"?

732
00:32:43,044 --> 00:32:43,920
You're good.

733
00:32:44,879 --> 00:32:45,755
Did you take lessons?

734
00:32:46,547 --> 00:32:47,382
For a month.

735
00:32:47,465 --> 00:32:50,969
A lot of boys start playing the guitar
in middle school.

736
00:32:51,803 --> 00:32:53,054
-You too?
-Me too.

737
00:33:09,237 --> 00:33:10,863
<i>I was so surprised.</i>

738
00:33:10,947 --> 00:33:12,824
<i>He can sing like this?</i>

739
00:33:12,907 --> 00:33:13,783
JUN-SEUNG STARTS SINGING

740
00:33:14,367 --> 00:33:15,868
You have a really nice voice.

741
00:33:15,952 --> 00:33:16,786
Sing later too.

742
00:33:16,869 --> 00:33:18,162
I can't sing over there.

743
00:33:18,246 --> 00:33:19,914
I get nervous.

744
00:33:19,998 --> 00:33:21,374
You won't sing later?

745
00:33:21,457 --> 00:33:22,333
I should.

746
00:33:22,417 --> 00:33:24,168
-You should.
-Should I practice?

747
00:33:24,252 --> 00:33:25,586
He's good.

748
00:33:26,879 --> 00:33:27,964
He's very good.

749
00:33:29,173 --> 00:33:30,633
He sounds like a singer.

750
00:33:31,134 --> 00:33:33,219
We can't even play one second of it?

751
00:33:33,302 --> 00:33:35,263
Netflix doesn't allow it
due to copyright issues.

752
00:33:35,346 --> 00:33:38,057
Why is he singing this
to the wrong person?

753
00:33:38,141 --> 00:33:39,642
He should do this for Ji-young!

754
00:33:39,726 --> 00:33:41,894
Who knows how things will change
because of this?

755
00:33:41,978 --> 00:33:43,646
It'd be fun if they developed feelings.

756
00:33:45,314 --> 00:33:47,859
<i>He sang so well</i>
<i>and played the guitar so well.</i>

757
00:33:47,942 --> 00:33:49,986
<i>We decided that he should</i>

758
00:33:50,069 --> 00:33:51,821
<i>play this to Ji-young tonight,</i>

759
00:33:51,904 --> 00:33:54,365
<i>so his performance started</i>
<i>from practicing for that.</i>

760
00:34:02,290 --> 00:34:04,333
<i>Then he looked so attractive.</i>

761
00:34:06,586 --> 00:34:08,212
<i>I found him cool.</i>

762
00:34:08,713 --> 00:34:10,089
I was so surprised.

763
00:34:10,173 --> 00:34:12,675
When you scratch on the surface,
you keep finding something.

764
00:34:12,759 --> 00:34:14,844
<i>He's articulate and a great cook.</i>

765
00:34:16,637 --> 00:34:18,181
<i>He's very playful too.</i>

766
00:34:19,098 --> 00:34:21,184
When you expect just one thing,

767
00:34:21,267 --> 00:34:22,810
you get ten things from him.

768
00:34:22,894 --> 00:34:25,855
If he had been like that from the start,

769
00:34:27,106 --> 00:34:28,691
things may have gone differently.

770
00:34:31,611 --> 00:34:32,653
We had a really good time.

771
00:34:33,529 --> 00:34:34,906
What if I end up falling for him?

772
00:34:36,324 --> 00:34:38,201
<i>It may start off as being</i>
<i>fond of him as a person</i>

773
00:34:38,785 --> 00:34:41,245
<i>but develop into something more romantic.</i>

774
00:34:41,329 --> 00:34:42,830
But for now,

775
00:34:42,914 --> 00:34:45,708
the two of us have
such big crushes on other people.

776
00:34:45,792 --> 00:34:46,751
I know.

777
00:34:46,834 --> 00:34:47,835
Yeah, it feels like that.

778
00:34:47,919 --> 00:34:50,046
If Si-hyun sang that well,

779
00:34:50,129 --> 00:34:51,547
-it wouldn't be surprising.
-Right.

780
00:34:51,631 --> 00:34:52,757
But it's Jun-seung.

781
00:34:52,840 --> 00:34:54,675
We expected that awkward person

782
00:34:54,759 --> 00:34:57,303
to sing awkwardly with his awkward hands,

783
00:34:57,386 --> 00:34:58,846
but he turned out to be super slick.

784
00:34:59,430 --> 00:35:00,264
I like that.

785
00:35:00,348 --> 00:35:03,017
If Jun-seung showed
just a bit of interest to Hyun-jin,

786
00:35:03,101 --> 00:35:04,769
she would develop feelings for him.

787
00:35:04,852 --> 00:35:06,771
-But he's been so firm about…
-Yeah.

788
00:35:06,854 --> 00:35:08,356
Because he only went for Ji-young,

789
00:35:08,439 --> 00:35:10,900
Hyun-jin thought there wasn't a chance.

790
00:35:10,983 --> 00:35:12,985
If he flirted with her just a bit,
she would have

791
00:35:13,069 --> 00:35:14,654
-fallen for it.
-Even just a bit of flirting.

792
00:35:14,737 --> 00:35:17,406
But we have five hours left.

793
00:35:17,490 --> 00:35:18,574
Who knows what'll happen?

794
00:35:18,658 --> 00:35:19,909
They'll be by themselves, at that.

795
00:35:21,536 --> 00:35:22,703
Plenty of time to fall for each other.

796
00:35:25,623 --> 00:35:26,791
Do you miss him?

797
00:35:26,874 --> 00:35:27,708
No.

798
00:35:28,417 --> 00:35:30,586
Do I miss him? I don't really remember.

799
00:35:30,670 --> 00:35:32,004
You don't remember his face?

800
00:35:32,088 --> 00:35:32,964
I remember his face.

801
00:35:33,047 --> 00:35:34,423
I can, now that I've tried to.

802
00:35:35,133 --> 00:35:37,760
Six hours? They must have gone very far.

803
00:35:39,137 --> 00:35:40,096
What if they went home?

804
00:35:40,179 --> 00:35:42,557
What if you went out for six hours?

805
00:35:42,640 --> 00:35:44,433
What would you do
if you could do what you want?

806
00:35:46,352 --> 00:35:47,603
I'd have to think about it.

807
00:35:47,687 --> 00:35:49,021
Maybe go see the ocean?

808
00:35:49,105 --> 00:35:50,189
It'll be memorable.

809
00:35:50,898 --> 00:35:53,526
The firsts are always memorable.

810
00:35:53,609 --> 00:35:54,694
And it's my first time

811
00:35:55,361 --> 00:35:57,196
-in Gangneung.
-What?

812
00:35:57,280 --> 00:35:58,156
It's my first time here.

813
00:35:58,239 --> 00:35:59,407
-Really?
-Yeah.

814
00:35:59,490 --> 00:36:03,870
The person you experience
your first with is also memorable.

815
00:36:04,453 --> 00:36:05,913
-What do you wear when you work?
-What?

816
00:36:05,997 --> 00:36:07,456
-What do you wear?
-Workwear.

817
00:36:09,333 --> 00:36:12,128
And if I'm welding something,
I have to wear something on top of that.

818
00:36:12,211 --> 00:36:14,422
It must be so hard in the summer.

819
00:36:14,505 --> 00:36:17,258
It feels suffocating
when you’re on top of a burning pit.

820
00:36:17,341 --> 00:36:19,719
When I sit there, I can see the heat wave.

821
00:36:20,261 --> 00:36:21,846
-Wow.
-That's my life.

822
00:36:22,722 --> 00:36:24,098
It's nothing special.

823
00:36:24,182 --> 00:36:25,808
<i>You know what's interesting?</i>

824
00:36:25,892 --> 00:36:27,310
<i>When he said he was a welder,</i>

825
00:36:27,393 --> 00:36:29,187
I thought he just melted stuff.

826
00:36:29,270 --> 00:36:32,356
But he said he works over a fire pit.

827
00:36:32,440 --> 00:36:33,524
It's just fire.

828
00:36:34,108 --> 00:36:36,152
Si-hyun, who left,

829
00:36:36,235 --> 00:36:37,403
works in water.

830
00:36:37,486 --> 00:36:38,738
He works in the water.

831
00:36:38,821 --> 00:36:40,114
They're so different.

832
00:36:40,198 --> 00:36:42,658
JI-YOUNG AND SI-HYUN
CHUAM BEACH

833
00:36:42,742 --> 00:36:44,702
-It's a long stretch.
-Shall we walk?

834
00:36:44,785 --> 00:36:48,581
When I was in that house,
I didn't think of life out here at all.

835
00:36:48,664 --> 00:36:50,708
-But now that we're out here,
-Yeah.

836
00:36:50,791 --> 00:36:52,710
it feels so refreshing.

837
00:36:52,793 --> 00:36:53,669
-Right?
-Yeah.

838
00:36:53,753 --> 00:36:55,671
It really feels like an escape.

839
00:36:57,131 --> 00:36:58,174
I don't want to go back.

840
00:36:58,883 --> 00:37:01,093
One, two, three.

841
00:37:02,678 --> 00:37:04,222
Just move your gaze toward me.

842
00:37:05,723 --> 00:37:06,891
Tuck in your chin a bit.

843
00:37:08,267 --> 00:37:09,769
-You're good at it.
-It isn't good?

844
00:37:09,852 --> 00:37:11,812
<i>No, you're good at it.</i>

845
00:37:13,105 --> 00:37:14,941
Wow. Look!

846
00:37:18,736 --> 00:37:20,154
You're pretty skilled.

847
00:37:20,238 --> 00:37:22,073
The model makes the picture.

848
00:37:22,156 --> 00:37:23,824
No, the photographer makes the picture.

849
00:37:23,908 --> 00:37:25,451
No, it's the model.

850
00:37:26,202 --> 00:37:28,287
-Should we dip our feet?
-Throw you in?

851
00:37:28,371 --> 00:37:30,081
<i>I think we joked around a lot.</i>

852
00:37:30,164 --> 00:37:32,083
Want to wear this?

853
00:37:32,708 --> 00:37:34,001
It'll be warm.

854
00:37:34,085 --> 00:37:35,294
-Should I just drape it over?
-Sure.

855
00:37:36,212 --> 00:37:37,546
I should throw you in.

856
00:37:37,630 --> 00:37:39,257
Throw me in?

857
00:37:39,340 --> 00:37:43,177
<i>I feel like we talked a lot</i>
<i>about small, everyday things</i>

858
00:37:43,261 --> 00:37:45,388
<i>like couples would.</i>

859
00:37:45,471 --> 00:37:48,933
<i>So it felt like we were a real couple.</i>

860
00:37:52,311 --> 00:37:55,189
How many hours do we have left?

861
00:37:56,899 --> 00:37:57,817
You want to hurry back?

862
00:37:57,900 --> 00:37:59,277
No.

863
00:37:59,360 --> 00:38:00,778
-Time flies.
-Just say the word.

864
00:38:02,280 --> 00:38:04,156
JI-YOUNG AND SI-HYUN
EUNHYE RAW FISH RESTAURANT

865
00:38:04,240 --> 00:38:05,825
-It's <i>hoe</i>.
-Come this way.

866
00:38:05,908 --> 00:38:07,702
-I'm hungry.
-I'm hungry.

867
00:38:11,122 --> 00:38:13,374
<i>The beach in Gangwon-do is the best.</i>

868
00:38:13,457 --> 00:38:14,333
<i>It's nice.</i>

869
00:38:14,417 --> 00:38:15,334
A DATE SPOT THAT LOOKS OVER THE OCEAN

870
00:38:16,669 --> 00:38:19,255
-Do I deserve this luxury?
-Right?

871
00:38:20,965 --> 00:38:22,633
It's because you're popular.

872
00:38:22,717 --> 00:38:23,759
Sorry?

873
00:38:23,843 --> 00:38:26,637
You could choose
because you got the most chips.

874
00:38:26,721 --> 00:38:28,139
I am thankful for that.

875
00:38:28,222 --> 00:38:29,140
The thing is,

876
00:38:29,223 --> 00:38:33,144
I think the reason why you got

877
00:38:33,227 --> 00:38:36,564
-the most chips is Hyun-jin.
-Why?

878
00:38:36,647 --> 00:38:39,859
-I know how much I put in yours, right?
-Yeah.

879
00:38:40,443 --> 00:38:43,070
But Jun-seung put in a lot

880
00:38:43,154 --> 00:38:44,447
-as well.
-Yeah.

881
00:38:44,530 --> 00:38:47,575
But you received even more than that.

882
00:38:50,578 --> 00:38:51,579
-You're right.
-Yeah.

883
00:38:51,662 --> 00:38:53,831
Anyway, for me,

884
00:38:54,457 --> 00:38:56,042
what matters is the final decision.

885
00:38:56,125 --> 00:38:59,003
What about you?
Is your mind pretty much made up?

886
00:38:59,086 --> 00:39:01,964
I don't think I ever asked you

887
00:39:02,048 --> 00:39:04,091
how you feel about me.

888
00:39:04,925 --> 00:39:06,761
-Are you asking me now?
-Yeah.

889
00:39:08,596 --> 00:39:13,100
I think my mind
will be made up by tonight.

890
00:39:13,726 --> 00:39:15,019
I'm scared to go back.

891
00:39:16,979 --> 00:39:18,064
Thank you.

892
00:39:18,147 --> 00:39:19,690
-Thank you.
-Pasta, right?

893
00:39:19,774 --> 00:39:22,026
What's this? Interesting.

894
00:39:23,819 --> 00:39:25,112
Thank you.

895
00:39:28,407 --> 00:39:29,533
It's good.

896
00:39:29,617 --> 00:39:31,035
Shall we have a drink?

897
00:39:31,118 --> 00:39:31,952
Sounds good.

898
00:39:33,245 --> 00:39:34,705
-Let's take our time.
-Okay.

899
00:39:35,289 --> 00:39:37,750
Let's take our time, chatting and eating.

900
00:39:37,833 --> 00:39:39,377
We can be an hour late.

901
00:39:40,378 --> 00:39:42,505
-How many more hours do you want?
-Two more hours.

902
00:39:43,005 --> 00:39:44,298
I'll take that and add two more.

903
00:39:45,591 --> 00:39:47,593
"Take that and add two more"? Nice one.

904
00:39:47,676 --> 00:39:49,095
-Was that good?
-Yeah.

905
00:39:49,637 --> 00:39:50,930
"Phew"?

906
00:39:51,514 --> 00:39:52,348
Phew.

907
00:39:52,890 --> 00:39:57,853
Do you think you're different
around Hyun-jin compared to

908
00:39:57,937 --> 00:39:58,979
when you're around me?

909
00:39:59,063 --> 00:40:00,356
I'm completely different.

910
00:40:00,439 --> 00:40:01,982
When I'm with Hyun-jin,

911
00:40:02,858 --> 00:40:04,068
I become serious.

912
00:40:04,693 --> 00:40:08,239
I have to think twice before I speak.

913
00:40:08,322 --> 00:40:10,741
<i>When I talked with Hyun-jin,</i>

914
00:40:10,825 --> 00:40:14,870
I'd have to always think twice
and I didn't feel that comfortable.

915
00:40:14,954 --> 00:40:18,290
But when I was chatting with Ji-young,

916
00:40:18,374 --> 00:40:20,751
I found myself at ease.

917
00:40:20,835 --> 00:40:24,380
<i>We exchanged a lot of funny jokes as well.</i>

918
00:40:24,964 --> 00:40:26,590
You see,

919
00:40:26,674 --> 00:40:30,469
I couldn't really tell if that was

920
00:40:30,553 --> 00:40:34,098
a positive thing or kind of negative.

921
00:40:34,181 --> 00:40:36,684
It felt like he was
beating around the bush.

922
00:40:37,935 --> 00:40:38,769
What about you?

923
00:40:38,853 --> 00:40:40,896
-Comparing you to Jun-seung?
-Yeah.

924
00:40:40,980 --> 00:40:43,149
With Jun-seung, it feels like

925
00:40:43,983 --> 00:40:45,401
we're just friends.

926
00:40:46,527 --> 00:40:47,486
With you,

927
00:40:47,570 --> 00:40:51,073
I feel the way I used to feel

928
00:40:51,157 --> 00:40:52,783
when I was in a relationship in the past.

929
00:40:52,867 --> 00:40:54,660
-With me?
-Yeah.

930
00:40:54,743 --> 00:40:56,829
The way we talk

931
00:40:56,912 --> 00:40:59,582
and mess around. Things like that.

932
00:41:02,251 --> 00:41:03,377
This is fun.

933
00:41:09,592 --> 00:41:10,801
You don't like lettuce wraps?

934
00:41:11,427 --> 00:41:13,262
-I like them.
-You do?

935
00:41:14,013 --> 00:41:15,639
After this, I'll have a wrap.

936
00:41:18,851 --> 00:41:20,311
<i>When I saw</i>

937
00:41:20,394 --> 00:41:23,105
<i>Si-hyun make the lettuce wrap,</i>

938
00:41:23,689 --> 00:41:28,360
<i>I wasn't thinking much about it</i>
<i>as I thought it was for him.</i>

939
00:41:28,444 --> 00:41:29,278
Have this.

940
00:41:36,035 --> 00:41:38,037
<i>But he made a lettuce wrap for me.</i>

941
00:41:38,621 --> 00:41:39,455
So

942
00:41:40,080 --> 00:41:41,123
I ate it off of his hand.

943
00:41:44,418 --> 00:41:45,461
Want me to make you one?

944
00:41:45,961 --> 00:41:47,880
-Shall we make one for each other?
-Okay.

945
00:41:48,547 --> 00:41:49,798
Dip it in this sauce?

946
00:41:50,633 --> 00:41:51,634
Sure.

947
00:41:55,471 --> 00:41:56,347
Shall I try yours first?

948
00:42:05,689 --> 00:42:07,358
-It's bound to be good.
-Yeah.

949
00:42:08,734 --> 00:42:13,197
DID YOU KEEP MAKING
EACH OTHER LETTUCE WRAPS?

950
00:42:13,280 --> 00:42:16,825
I don't think we made our own wraps.

951
00:42:16,909 --> 00:42:19,745
We kept making it for each other.

952
00:42:19,828 --> 00:42:23,207
<i>It really did feel like a date</i>

953
00:42:23,290 --> 00:42:25,042
<i>you'd have with a boyfriend.</i>

954
00:42:31,215 --> 00:42:32,591
Should we make time stand still?

955
00:42:39,265 --> 00:42:41,725
It looks like your eyeballs are moving.

956
00:42:41,809 --> 00:42:43,310
You failed just now, didn't you?

957
00:42:43,394 --> 00:42:45,062
I went like this, but your eyes moved.

958
00:42:49,483 --> 00:42:51,485
<i>I'd talk to her, lock eyes with her,</i>
<i>and would just smile.</i>

959
00:42:51,569 --> 00:42:52,861
You weren't quite perfect.

960
00:42:53,946 --> 00:42:57,658
I think that's why I felt
it was a comfortable conversation.

961
00:42:57,741 --> 00:43:00,661
It felt like a very comfortable date.

962
00:43:01,453 --> 00:43:02,997
What will it be like when we get back?

963
00:43:03,831 --> 00:43:05,583
I don't think it's right to act like

964
00:43:06,792 --> 00:43:09,503
-we had so much fun.
-Right, we both shouldn't.

965
00:43:10,254 --> 00:43:11,547
I'm having such a good time.

966
00:43:12,631 --> 00:43:14,508
I'm not really thinking
about the people back there,

967
00:43:14,592 --> 00:43:16,510
but it may change when I get back.

968
00:43:17,344 --> 00:43:22,308
When you make up your mind this evening,

969
00:43:22,391 --> 00:43:24,435
you'll have to make your stance clear

970
00:43:25,019 --> 00:43:26,895
-so as not to confuse the other person.
-Right.

971
00:43:27,438 --> 00:43:29,940
Do you think you'll be clear
about how you feel then?

972
00:43:30,024 --> 00:43:31,483
Yeah, when I make up my mind.

973
00:43:32,359 --> 00:43:34,278
Man, I guess I'll lose sleep tonight.

974
00:43:34,903 --> 00:43:36,363
I have a lot on my mind.

975
00:43:40,451 --> 00:43:42,828
<i>If he felt sure he liked Hyun-jin,</i>

976
00:43:42,911 --> 00:43:47,041
I don't think he would have
fed me, taken care of me,

977
00:43:47,124 --> 00:43:49,168
and done things like that.

978
00:43:49,251 --> 00:43:52,254
Since he showed that side to me,

979
00:43:52,338 --> 00:43:54,423
I wondered if he had feelings for me too.

980
00:43:54,506 --> 00:43:58,218
Is he not completely invested in Hyun-jin?

981
00:43:58,302 --> 00:44:01,972
Perhaps I can win him over.

982
00:44:02,556 --> 00:44:04,058
<i>Those thoughts crossed my mind.</i>

983
00:44:07,811 --> 00:44:09,313
He clearly has feelings for her.

984
00:44:09,396 --> 00:44:11,106
He wouldn't make a wrap if he didn't.

985
00:44:11,190 --> 00:44:12,524
It'd be crazy if he didn't have feelings.

986
00:44:12,608 --> 00:44:14,276
Ji-young keeps wondering

987
00:44:14,360 --> 00:44:17,071
how strong his feelings are
for Hyun-jin and her, respectively.

988
00:44:17,154 --> 00:44:18,197
She'll know this evening.

989
00:44:19,948 --> 00:44:22,743
Is he playing the game Mafia?
He'll let her know by nightfall?

990
00:44:22,826 --> 00:44:24,286
You're an "it guy."

991
00:44:24,787 --> 00:44:26,497
FLICKING

992
00:44:26,580 --> 00:44:27,539
Oh, look at you.

993
00:44:27,623 --> 00:44:28,832
Acting pitiful.

994
00:44:28,916 --> 00:44:31,669
Ouch. It hurts a bit here.

995
00:44:32,336 --> 00:44:33,712
-I'm sad.
-I'm so sad.

996
00:44:33,796 --> 00:44:34,880
"I'm sad" with a lisp. Like that?

997
00:44:34,963 --> 00:44:36,757
-I hate that.
-No hands though.

998
00:44:38,634 --> 00:44:41,095
Do you feel so much at ease
around Ji-young too?

999
00:44:41,887 --> 00:44:43,055
I get all flustered.

1000
00:44:43,138 --> 00:44:45,641
She may like that you get flustered.

1001
00:44:45,724 --> 00:44:48,227
But I bet she doesn't even realize
that I get flustered.

1002
00:44:48,310 --> 00:44:50,687
-Since she doesn't know this side of you.
-Exactly. She has no idea.

1003
00:44:50,771 --> 00:44:52,648
She's only seen you being flustered.

1004
00:44:52,731 --> 00:44:53,857
"What's up with this guy?"

1005
00:44:53,941 --> 00:44:56,235
-"He's acting weird."
-That's all she knows.

1006
00:44:56,318 --> 00:44:59,113
-Isn't it about time they got back?
-They must be having fun.

1007
00:44:59,196 --> 00:45:00,280
Be careful.

1008
00:45:04,576 --> 00:45:07,538
LOOKING AT HER PHOTO GALLERY

1009
00:45:21,760 --> 00:45:23,178
<i>-It was like a dream.</i>
<i>-Yeah.</i>

1010
00:45:23,846 --> 00:45:25,472
<i>Yeah, wake up.</i>

1011
00:45:27,933 --> 00:45:30,144
I'm really curious
what they've been up to.

1012
00:45:30,227 --> 00:45:31,937
Are you finally getting curious?

1013
00:45:32,729 --> 00:45:35,190
You have nowhere to escape now.

1014
00:45:37,401 --> 00:45:38,360
<i>I was torn.</i>

1015
00:45:38,444 --> 00:45:39,820
I didn't want to go back,

1016
00:45:39,903 --> 00:45:41,238
but I also wanted to go back

1017
00:45:41,321 --> 00:45:44,366
and have a chat with Hyun-jin as well.

1018
00:45:47,494 --> 00:45:48,787
Let's say

1019
00:45:48,871 --> 00:45:51,623
there's someone who's coy like a fox
but acts clumsy like a bear

1020
00:45:51,707 --> 00:45:53,333
and there's someone
who's clumsy like a bear

1021
00:45:53,417 --> 00:45:55,085
but acts coy like a fox.
Which do you prefer?

1022
00:45:55,169 --> 00:45:56,545
Which do I prefer?

1023
00:45:56,628 --> 00:45:59,256
Definitely the bear acting like a fox.

1024
00:46:00,257 --> 00:46:02,551
I think you're the bear

1025
00:46:02,634 --> 00:46:05,220
that wants to be like a fox.

1026
00:46:06,513 --> 00:46:07,931
You're right. I <i>am</i> like a bear.

1027
00:46:08,015 --> 00:46:09,558
Yeah, I think you are.

1028
00:46:09,641 --> 00:46:10,517
What am I like?

1029
00:46:11,143 --> 00:46:11,977
You?

1030
00:46:12,603 --> 00:46:13,896
I think you're like a bear too.

1031
00:46:14,521 --> 00:46:15,898
I'm very much like a fox.

1032
00:46:16,482 --> 00:46:19,151
Saying that itself means he's a fox.

1033
00:46:19,234 --> 00:46:20,819
A bear wouldn't make a wrap for her.

1034
00:46:21,320 --> 00:46:22,362
It's cute, though.

1035
00:46:25,240 --> 00:46:26,325
That's why you're a bear.

1036
00:46:29,077 --> 00:46:30,370
I'm very much like a fox.

1037
00:46:31,371 --> 00:46:33,457
You're a fox? I'm not so sure.

1038
00:46:33,540 --> 00:46:35,751
Do you notice how I feel?

1039
00:46:35,834 --> 00:46:36,960
Not really.

1040
00:46:37,044 --> 00:46:38,170
You see?

1041
00:46:39,421 --> 00:46:40,631
I don't really see it.

1042
00:46:41,256 --> 00:46:42,174
I can't tell

1043
00:46:43,634 --> 00:46:44,510
how you feel.

1044
00:46:46,637 --> 00:46:48,013
You'll find out when we get there.

1045
00:46:52,100 --> 00:46:53,352
What about Hyun-jin?

1046
00:46:53,435 --> 00:46:54,770
What is she?

1047
00:46:55,270 --> 00:46:57,105
Why does she keep asking
about someone else?

1048
00:46:57,189 --> 00:46:58,815
She keeps bringing up Hyun-jin.

1049
00:46:58,899 --> 00:47:00,943
-She's wondering how he feels about her.
-Yeah.

1050
00:47:01,527 --> 00:47:02,736
What about Hyun-jin?

1051
00:47:02,819 --> 00:47:04,196
What is she?

1052
00:47:05,989 --> 00:47:07,741
She definitely isn't like a fox.

1053
00:47:09,618 --> 00:47:10,452
She's just a boss lady.

1054
00:47:11,411 --> 00:47:12,246
"Boss lady"?

1055
00:47:12,996 --> 00:47:15,874
I like someone who has a backbone.

1056
00:47:17,292 --> 00:47:21,129
Someone who can be honest with me
and not just considerate.

1057
00:47:21,213 --> 00:47:23,131
"I like this. I don't like that."

1058
00:47:23,215 --> 00:47:26,134
I think it's important in life to know

1059
00:47:26,218 --> 00:47:27,928
what I like and dislike.

1060
00:47:28,595 --> 00:47:30,097
Even when you're making a choice.

1061
00:47:32,391 --> 00:47:34,726
<i>People used to say</i>
<i>that I have a backbone.</i>

1062
00:47:34,810 --> 00:47:37,104
<i>I was very straightforward</i>
<i>about what I like or dislike.</i>

1063
00:47:37,187 --> 00:47:38,188
<i>But the thing is,</i>

1064
00:47:38,272 --> 00:47:42,859
when I'm with someone I really like,
I kind of become spineless.

1065
00:47:43,443 --> 00:47:45,529
He gave me the courage

1066
00:47:45,612 --> 00:47:46,947
to express my feelings

1067
00:47:48,282 --> 00:47:49,491
to him clearly.

1068
00:47:49,575 --> 00:47:50,867
<i>Aren't you tired?</i>

1069
00:47:50,951 --> 00:47:52,202
<i>I think I am tired.</i>

1070
00:47:52,286 --> 00:47:53,912
<i>Get a shut-eye until we get there.</i>

1071
00:48:10,262 --> 00:48:11,513
Did he touch her ear?

1072
00:48:11,597 --> 00:48:13,265
Didn't he just hold her head?

1073
00:48:14,182 --> 00:48:15,350
He can't do that!

1074
00:48:16,935 --> 00:48:18,562
Darn it. That hurts.

1075
00:48:18,645 --> 00:48:21,023
That gives you crazy butterflies.

1076
00:48:25,485 --> 00:48:28,405
<i>I closed my eyes, then I fell asleep.</i>

1077
00:48:28,488 --> 00:48:33,452
<i>And Si-hyun supported my head</i>
<i>from falling to the side.</i>

1078
00:48:35,078 --> 00:48:37,080
I was a bit surprised.

1079
00:48:37,664 --> 00:48:39,249
Since it was just the two of us,

1080
00:48:39,333 --> 00:48:42,461
he looked after me more attentively.

1081
00:48:42,544 --> 00:48:44,004
Everything about the date

1082
00:48:44,963 --> 00:48:46,506
gave me butterflies.

1083
00:48:46,590 --> 00:48:47,716
It was fun.

1084
00:48:48,592 --> 00:48:51,261
I think I'll remember the date
for a long time.

1085
00:48:54,973 --> 00:48:57,184
-I suppose they'll be back soon.
-You think so?

1086
00:48:57,267 --> 00:48:59,353
Will they have eaten?

1087
00:48:59,436 --> 00:49:01,521
If they want to eat,
I can start on the curry.

1088
00:49:01,605 --> 00:49:03,231
Ji-young said she wanted curry.

1089
00:49:03,315 --> 00:49:04,608
She was looking forward to it.

1090
00:49:05,859 --> 00:49:06,735
Should we make it?

1091
00:49:06,818 --> 00:49:08,695
He kept going on about curry all day.

1092
00:49:08,779 --> 00:49:10,280
Let's eat the curry later.

1093
00:49:10,364 --> 00:49:11,531
For dinner.

1094
00:49:11,615 --> 00:49:12,991
I'm going to eat a yummy dinner.

1095
00:49:13,075 --> 00:49:14,034
Curry.

1096
00:49:14,117 --> 00:49:15,827
If they want to eat something--

1097
00:49:15,911 --> 00:49:16,995
They have to eat curry.

1098
00:49:17,079 --> 00:49:18,789
That was a lot of guitar for me.

1099
00:49:18,872 --> 00:49:22,209
I'll play it again during dinner
over some curry.

1100
00:49:22,292 --> 00:49:24,544
So I thought,
"Okay, let's make that curry."

1101
00:49:25,170 --> 00:49:26,838
Shall we start making it then?

1102
00:49:26,922 --> 00:49:27,839
Shall we?

1103
00:49:28,840 --> 00:49:29,966
Which meat should I use?

1104
00:49:30,050 --> 00:49:31,468
We should make a lot

1105
00:49:31,551 --> 00:49:32,844
if we want it for breakfast too.

1106
00:49:32,928 --> 00:49:33,845
Let's put it all in.

1107
00:49:33,929 --> 00:49:35,013
Rich people curry.

1108
00:49:35,097 --> 00:49:36,765
Should we add some potatoes?

1109
00:49:36,848 --> 00:49:38,266
Is it going well?

1110
00:49:38,350 --> 00:49:39,935
Would you like to smell it?

1111
00:49:40,018 --> 00:49:41,478
<i>I was helping him out too.</i>

1112
00:49:41,561 --> 00:49:43,230
But I really don't like curry.

1113
00:49:45,732 --> 00:49:46,900
<i>For a split second, I wondered,</i>

1114
00:49:47,734 --> 00:49:49,361
<i>"What am I doing here?"</i>

1115
00:49:52,114 --> 00:49:54,324
<i>I was making curry feeling unmotivated.</i>

1116
00:49:54,408 --> 00:49:55,701
I should let it sit here for a while.

1117
00:49:57,244 --> 00:49:58,704
It smells nice. Looking good too.

1118
00:49:58,787 --> 00:50:02,290
If they can't eat it tonight,
feed it to them for breakfast.

1119
00:50:02,374 --> 00:50:03,542
-Those two?
-Yeah.

1120
00:50:05,001 --> 00:50:07,546
<i>If they ask what we did,</i>
<i>should we say it's a secret?</i>

1121
00:50:08,839 --> 00:50:10,090
<i>-"It's a secret."</i>
<i>-"It's a secret."</i>

1122
00:50:11,133 --> 00:50:12,634
We didn't get to

1123
00:50:12,718 --> 00:50:14,803
-eat Jun-seung's curry in the end.
-No, we didn't.

1124
00:50:15,429 --> 00:50:17,305
We're back.

1125
00:50:18,140 --> 00:50:19,641
-We're back.
-You're back.

1126
00:50:19,725 --> 00:50:20,976
We're back.

1127
00:50:21,059 --> 00:50:22,936
-Welcome back.
-I smell curry.

1128
00:50:23,520 --> 00:50:25,939
-For real.
-I've been making curry.

1129
00:50:26,022 --> 00:50:27,441
You haven't eaten yet?

1130
00:50:27,524 --> 00:50:28,775
We had lunch.

1131
00:50:28,859 --> 00:50:29,943
You haven't had dinner yet?

1132
00:50:30,026 --> 00:50:31,236
Did you already eat?

1133
00:50:32,279 --> 00:50:33,905
-I wanted to try your curry.
-Yeah.

1134
00:50:33,989 --> 00:50:35,073
So you did eat.

1135
00:50:36,032 --> 00:50:37,659
What did you do today?

1136
00:50:37,743 --> 00:50:39,661
-Why are you acting so formal?
-Oh, yeah.

1137
00:50:45,792 --> 00:50:48,170
-You sense crazy tension here, right?
-Yeah.

1138
00:50:48,253 --> 00:50:49,254
What is this?

1139
00:50:49,337 --> 00:50:51,089
This looks like a movie poster.

1140
00:50:51,173 --> 00:50:52,424
Right now,

1141
00:50:52,507 --> 00:50:55,594
Ji-young is looking back at them,
he's doing the dishes…

1142
00:50:55,677 --> 00:50:56,928
This is insane.

1143
00:50:59,431 --> 00:51:00,974
-You're here.
-Hi.

1144
00:51:01,057 --> 00:51:02,017
Hello.

1145
00:51:03,143 --> 00:51:05,187
-What did you do?
-The curry smell is super strong.

1146
00:51:14,613 --> 00:51:16,031
I'm hungry.

1147
00:51:16,114 --> 00:51:17,157
You didn't eat yet?

1148
00:51:17,741 --> 00:51:18,992
I wanted to try the curry.

1149
00:51:19,534 --> 00:51:21,161
It looks like they've already eaten.

1150
00:51:21,244 --> 00:51:22,120
Taste it.

1151
00:51:23,538 --> 00:51:24,372
-It's hot.
-Okay.

1152
00:51:26,082 --> 00:51:27,793
-Is it good?
-Yeah.

1153
00:51:28,335 --> 00:51:29,878
That's it.

1154
00:51:29,961 --> 00:51:30,837
So good.

1155
00:51:30,921 --> 00:51:32,631
-So nice and smooth, right?
-Yeah.

1156
00:51:34,716 --> 00:51:36,134
<i>She wouldn't even make eye contact.</i>

1157
00:51:36,218 --> 00:51:38,011
<i>They were just busy making curry.</i>

1158
00:51:38,094 --> 00:51:39,888
<i>I was wondering what was going on.</i>

1159
00:51:39,971 --> 00:51:42,182
-I'll get changed.
-Okay.

1160
00:51:42,265 --> 00:51:44,976
I spoke to him formally
without even realizing it.

1161
00:51:45,560 --> 00:51:46,520
Is she washing up?

1162
00:51:47,687 --> 00:51:48,522
What?

1163
00:51:48,605 --> 00:51:50,232
Is Ji-young washing up?

1164
00:51:50,315 --> 00:51:51,399
She's brushing her teeth.

1165
00:51:52,192 --> 00:51:53,318
She spoke formally to him.

1166
00:51:53,819 --> 00:51:54,861
Why so formal?

1167
00:51:55,904 --> 00:51:57,572
What's going on here?

1168
00:51:57,656 --> 00:51:58,615
It's a bit awkward.

1169
00:51:58,698 --> 00:52:00,992
We're awkward
because you were gone for six hours.

1170
00:52:02,661 --> 00:52:03,995
<i>It felt so awkward.</i>

1171
00:52:04,579 --> 00:52:07,249
All of a sudden,
we were speaking formally.

1172
00:52:10,710 --> 00:52:11,711
Hello, there.

1173
00:52:12,712 --> 00:52:14,673
What's wrong?

1174
00:52:15,966 --> 00:52:17,384
What was your date like?

1175
00:52:19,010 --> 00:52:20,595
Can you not tell us?

1176
00:52:20,679 --> 00:52:22,222
You can find out when it airs.

1177
00:52:22,305 --> 00:52:24,307
-"Find out when it airs"?
-Yeah.

1178
00:52:27,811 --> 00:52:29,396
<i>"You can find out when it airs."</i>

1179
00:52:29,479 --> 00:52:30,814
<i>That's what she said. I wondered,</i>

1180
00:52:32,274 --> 00:52:33,149
"What's going on?"

1181
00:52:33,233 --> 00:52:37,737
After hearing that, I realized
that something may be going on

1182
00:52:37,821 --> 00:52:39,155
between those two.

1183
00:52:39,239 --> 00:52:42,868
I felt uncomfortable about revealing

1184
00:52:42,951 --> 00:52:43,994
that we filled ourselves

1185
00:52:44,077 --> 00:52:46,037
with delicious food on our date.

1186
00:52:46,663 --> 00:52:49,541
-Unbelievable.
-But they did eat a lot.

1187
00:52:49,624 --> 00:52:51,459
They must've eaten a lot
at the restaurant.

1188
00:52:52,377 --> 00:52:53,253
Thanks for dinner.

1189
00:52:53,336 --> 00:52:54,421
-Enjoy.
-Thank you.

1190
00:52:54,504 --> 00:52:56,423
-Thank you.
-Should I get some kimchi?

1191
00:52:56,506 --> 00:52:57,632
Do you want kimchi?

1192
00:52:57,716 --> 00:52:58,884
-I'm okay.
-I'm fine.

1193
00:52:58,967 --> 00:53:00,176
-I don't like kimchi.
-I'm okay.

1194
00:53:00,260 --> 00:53:01,303
Okay.

1195
00:53:01,386 --> 00:53:02,679
-Come back and sit.
-Sit.

1196
00:53:05,390 --> 00:53:07,684
I've never had this before.

1197
00:53:07,767 --> 00:53:08,894
What is it? Spicy…

1198
00:53:08,977 --> 00:53:10,687
-Slightly spicy?
-Slightly spicy.

1199
00:53:10,770 --> 00:53:12,147
Do the two of you like it?

1200
00:53:12,230 --> 00:53:13,857
-Do the two of you like it?
-Yeah.

1201
00:53:13,940 --> 00:53:14,858
Yeah.

1202
00:53:33,001 --> 00:53:34,461
-Is it good?
-Yes.

1203
00:53:34,544 --> 00:53:35,837
Okay. Eat up.

1204
00:53:39,090 --> 00:53:40,383
<i>I was full,</i>

1205
00:53:40,467 --> 00:53:42,385
but I felt like
if I said I didn't want any,

1206
00:53:42,469 --> 00:53:45,472
it would hurt Jun-seung's feelings.

1207
00:53:45,555 --> 00:53:47,182
And I felt uneasy too.

1208
00:53:47,265 --> 00:53:49,601
I think Si-hyun felt the same way too.

1209
00:53:52,604 --> 00:53:55,690
<i>I was very conscious of Hyun-jin.</i>

1210
00:53:55,774 --> 00:53:58,985
She seemed very subdued.

1211
00:54:01,529 --> 00:54:04,407
I was kind of worried about Jun-seung.

1212
00:54:04,491 --> 00:54:06,326
They're eating it,

1213
00:54:06,409 --> 00:54:10,372
but you could tell that
they were eating it to be polite.

1214
00:54:10,455 --> 00:54:13,083
So I was wondering if he was okay.

1215
00:54:16,503 --> 00:54:18,129
If you don't want it, give it to me.

1216
00:54:18,213 --> 00:54:20,090
You're just nibbling at it.

1217
00:54:21,091 --> 00:54:23,343
You know what? I use that method too.

1218
00:54:23,426 --> 00:54:25,804
You want to say something
to one person, but you say it to another.

1219
00:54:25,887 --> 00:54:27,973
He actually wants to say that
to the other two.

1220
00:54:28,056 --> 00:54:30,225
But if he said that to them,
it would make it awkward

1221
00:54:30,308 --> 00:54:32,352
so he said to Hyun-jin,
"You're just nibbling at it."

1222
00:54:32,435 --> 00:54:34,396
"Just give it to me."

1223
00:54:37,315 --> 00:54:38,900
If you don't want it, give it to me.

1224
00:54:38,984 --> 00:54:40,610
You're just nibbling at it.

1225
00:54:41,736 --> 00:54:43,154
I <i>am</i> eating it. Leave me alone.

1226
00:54:52,497 --> 00:54:53,707
<i>It's like we know them,</i>

1227
00:54:54,958 --> 00:54:56,918
but it felt like we became a bit distant.

1228
00:54:57,002 --> 00:54:58,962
I couldn't look them in the eyes.

1229
00:55:00,296 --> 00:55:01,297
<i>It's nighttime.</i>

1230
00:55:02,340 --> 00:55:03,883
<i>-What?</i>
<i>-It's nighttime.</i>

1231
00:55:16,604 --> 00:55:18,023
Man, what's up with this silence?

1232
00:55:19,733 --> 00:55:21,443
What on earth is going on?

1233
00:55:21,526 --> 00:55:23,486
It feels awkward since it's been a while.

1234
00:55:23,570 --> 00:55:25,238
-Right? Me too.
-Yeah.

1235
00:55:25,321 --> 00:55:26,906
-I feel distant.
-It feels weird.

1236
00:55:26,990 --> 00:55:28,033
What's up with the silence?

1237
00:55:28,116 --> 00:55:29,367
-Be formal again?
-It's a little weird.

1238
00:55:29,951 --> 00:55:31,286
They're acting so strange.

1239
00:55:31,369 --> 00:55:34,080
-I know. They're making it weird.
-Yeah.

1240
00:55:34,164 --> 00:55:36,916
-We're the only ones who've been talking.
-Yeah.

1241
00:55:37,000 --> 00:55:39,919
-No, what are you saying?
-No, that's not true.

1242
00:55:40,587 --> 00:55:42,672
What kind of date did you go on

1243
00:55:42,756 --> 00:55:45,091
that it's so awkward in here?

1244
00:55:46,009 --> 00:55:47,510
We went to a cafe,

1245
00:55:47,594 --> 00:55:49,471
then to the beach, and had some <i>hoe</i>.

1246
00:55:49,554 --> 00:55:51,347
We went to Samcheok.

1247
00:55:51,431 --> 00:55:53,433
It took a little over an hour.

1248
00:55:53,516 --> 00:55:56,895
<i>Yeah, it was the kind of date</i>
<i>that I think a couple would go on.</i>

1249
00:55:58,438 --> 00:55:59,606
I felt troubled.

1250
00:56:01,941 --> 00:56:05,695
Ji-young did say she wanted to
go on a date that couples would go on.

1251
00:56:05,779 --> 00:56:09,407
It felt like the two of them
got very close.

1252
00:56:09,491 --> 00:56:10,492
Yeah.

1253
00:56:10,575 --> 00:56:14,829
I realized that there may have been
a slight change in Ji-young's heart.

1254
00:56:16,664 --> 00:56:18,917
Thankfully, we didn't walk there.

1255
00:56:22,337 --> 00:56:23,588
Sounds fun.

1256
00:56:29,928 --> 00:56:33,681
I'm sure that those two
had way more fun than us,

1257
00:56:34,265 --> 00:56:35,600
but they tried not to show it.

1258
00:56:36,184 --> 00:56:37,727
That felt different

1259
00:56:37,811 --> 00:56:40,188
from when they got back
from the convenience store date.

1260
00:56:59,666 --> 00:57:02,377
Jun-seung and Ji-young's vibe

1261
00:57:02,460 --> 00:57:04,712
after they got back
from the convenience store date

1262
00:57:05,296 --> 00:57:07,215
was so different
from Si-hyun and Ji-young's vibe.

1263
00:57:11,511 --> 00:57:12,470
It felt strange.

1264
00:57:13,888 --> 00:57:17,016
And I started feeling awkward
around them as well.

1265
00:57:18,184 --> 00:57:21,062
Because I was with Jun-seung
the whole day, I started talking like him.

1266
00:57:21,146 --> 00:57:23,189
And because I was looking at him all day,

1267
00:57:23,273 --> 00:57:25,567
I couldn't even remember
what the other two looked like.

1268
00:57:26,359 --> 00:57:27,944
But when I saw them…

1269
00:57:39,581 --> 00:57:41,624
I figured they must've had fun.

1270
00:57:45,462 --> 00:57:47,213
-She must really like him.
-Yeah.

1271
00:57:47,297 --> 00:57:51,009
I think I'd be more emotional
if I was in there too

1272
00:57:51,092 --> 00:57:53,928
because being in touch
with your emotions is all you do there.

1273
00:57:54,012 --> 00:57:55,555
You're completely focused
on your emotions.

1274
00:57:55,638 --> 00:57:58,600
Usually, you have work and friends,
but in there…

1275
00:57:58,683 --> 00:58:00,685
-You have too much time to think.
-That's right.

1276
00:58:00,768 --> 00:58:03,521
The two that went out got to
hang out for seven hours.

1277
00:58:03,605 --> 00:58:07,275
Those two that were left behind thought
about the other two for seven hours

1278
00:58:07,358 --> 00:58:08,651
and made curry.

1279
00:58:19,037 --> 00:58:20,038
Should I play the guitar?

1280
00:58:20,747 --> 00:58:21,581
Yeah.

1281
00:58:22,790 --> 00:58:23,791
Any requests?

1282
00:58:24,667 --> 00:58:26,628
Play something you're good at.

1283
00:58:27,128 --> 00:58:28,421
Do I have to sing too?

1284
00:58:28,505 --> 00:58:29,464
Yeah.

1285
00:58:29,547 --> 00:58:30,798
Yeah? Okay.

1286
00:58:32,509 --> 00:58:33,801
I'm getting nervous.

1287
00:58:33,885 --> 00:58:34,886
Look away.

1288
00:58:34,969 --> 00:58:36,262
I'd be nervous too

1289
00:58:36,346 --> 00:58:37,388
if I were you.

1290
00:58:39,307 --> 00:58:41,059
-Just ease into it.
-Okay.

1291
00:58:41,142 --> 00:58:42,268
Suddenly?

1292
00:58:42,352 --> 00:58:44,270
I'll play some background music then.

1293
00:58:44,354 --> 00:58:45,396
-Okay.
-Hey.

1294
00:58:45,480 --> 00:58:46,397
Hang on.

1295
00:58:47,190 --> 00:58:48,233
What's this?

1296
00:58:48,942 --> 00:58:50,777
-A special benefit?
-No.

1297
00:58:50,860 --> 00:58:52,195
YOU'LL PLAY A LOVE MARBLE GAME
WITH A SPECIAL BENEFIT AT STAKE

1298
00:58:52,278 --> 00:58:53,112
What's this?

1299
00:58:53,196 --> 00:58:54,656
-Love Marble.
-Love Marble.

1300
00:58:54,739 --> 00:58:55,949
Marble?

1301
00:58:56,950 --> 00:58:59,536
<i>This is your last night,</i>
<i>and you'll play the Love Marble game.</i>

1302
00:59:02,205 --> 00:59:04,832
<i>Pick your game piece and roll the dice</i>

1303
00:59:05,875 --> 00:59:08,169
<i>to find out how</i>
<i>the other person is feeling.</i>

1304
00:59:08,795 --> 00:59:11,089
<i>The first person to finish</i>
<i>two laps of the board</i>

1305
00:59:11,172 --> 00:59:13,132
<i>will be given a special benefit.</i>

1306
00:59:13,716 --> 00:59:15,218
-Shall we go?
-Okay.

1307
00:59:16,219 --> 00:59:17,512
<i>What's going on?</i>

1308
00:59:17,595 --> 00:59:18,429
<i>What's this?</i>

1309
00:59:18,513 --> 00:59:20,557
<i>I couldn't really focus on that, though.</i>

1310
00:59:22,934 --> 00:59:24,769
Love Marble.

1311
00:59:25,562 --> 00:59:29,148
Is it similar to Blue Marble?

1312
00:59:29,232 --> 00:59:30,191
What is this?

1313
00:59:30,817 --> 00:59:31,776
<i>What is this?</i>

1314
00:59:31,859 --> 00:59:33,444
It's probably like Truth-or-Dare.

1315
00:59:33,528 --> 00:59:36,114
<i>I was happy because I got a chance</i>
<i>to ask questions.</i>

1316
00:59:36,698 --> 00:59:38,575
<i>When I saw the board,</i>

1317
00:59:40,201 --> 00:59:42,912
I didn't really care about trying to win.

1318
00:59:42,996 --> 00:59:46,124
I just wasn't in the mood to play.

1319
00:59:48,001 --> 00:59:49,335
Two laps.

1320
00:59:49,419 --> 00:59:51,963
<i>This is my last chance,</i>
<i>so I'm going to use this game to be</i>

1321
00:59:52,046 --> 00:59:56,759
be completely honest about my feelings
and make sure I have no regrets.

1322
00:59:56,843 --> 01:00:01,556
I wanted to know how Hyun-jin felt
through the game.

1323
01:00:01,639 --> 01:00:04,684
<i>When I saw Hyun-jin's face</i>
<i>when we got back…</i>

1324
01:00:04,767 --> 01:00:06,019
-You're here.
-Hi.

1325
01:00:06,102 --> 01:00:07,395
Hello.

1326
01:00:07,478 --> 01:00:09,772
<i>I wasn't completely indifferent about her,</i>

1327
01:00:09,856 --> 01:00:13,192
so I realized that even though I was
on a date with Ji-young for six hours,

1328
01:00:13,276 --> 01:00:15,987
<i>I still had some feelings for Hyun-jin.</i>

1329
01:00:17,196 --> 01:00:19,699
-Did everyone understand the rules?
-Yes.

1330
01:00:19,782 --> 01:00:20,700
Put it here.

1331
01:00:21,326 --> 01:00:23,578
Okay, let me pour a drink for everyone.

1332
01:00:23,661 --> 01:00:25,747
START

1333
01:00:28,666 --> 01:00:30,710
<i>-The eldest can go first.</i>
<i>-The eldest.</i>

1334
01:00:32,837 --> 01:00:34,756
-Clock-wise, starting with the winner?
-Okay.

1335
01:00:34,839 --> 01:00:36,382
-Rock-paper-scissors.
-Scissors.

1336
01:00:37,634 --> 01:00:38,468
-You go.
-Me?

1337
01:00:38,551 --> 01:00:39,469
-Yeah.
-Oh.

1338
01:00:40,094 --> 01:00:40,928
You're good.

1339
01:00:41,012 --> 01:00:42,096
HYUN-JIN

1340
01:00:42,180 --> 01:00:43,556
Oh my. Sorry about that.

1341
01:00:43,640 --> 01:00:47,560
"Say one thing you find attractive about
the two people of the opposite sex."

1342
01:00:51,689 --> 01:00:52,732
First of all,

1343
01:00:53,816 --> 01:00:55,193
-Jun-seung is
-Yes?

1344
01:00:55,777 --> 01:00:57,654
an exceptionally good singer.

1345
01:00:58,237 --> 01:00:59,364
And Si-hyun

1346
01:01:00,073 --> 01:01:01,115
is mature.

1347
01:01:02,408 --> 01:01:03,242
Yes.

1348
01:01:06,079 --> 01:01:07,789
SI-HYUN

1349
01:01:07,872 --> 01:01:10,625
"Ask one question to the person
of your choice."

1350
01:01:10,708 --> 01:01:12,835
"The person cannot reject it."

1351
01:01:12,919 --> 01:01:14,504
THE ROOM OF TRUTH

1352
01:01:14,587 --> 01:01:16,422
I pick Jun-seung.

1353
01:01:16,506 --> 01:01:17,924
-Show some respect.
-My bad.

1354
01:01:19,258 --> 01:01:21,386
How did you feel

1355
01:01:21,469 --> 01:01:23,471
during the six hours today?

1356
01:01:25,014 --> 01:01:27,058
I was feeling glad.

1357
01:01:28,976 --> 01:01:30,061
It was actually for the better.

1358
01:01:30,144 --> 01:01:31,938
So I was just glad.

1359
01:01:36,484 --> 01:01:38,277
JI-YOUNG

1360
01:01:38,361 --> 01:01:40,446
HAVE A NICE, COLD DRINK

1361
01:01:40,530 --> 01:01:43,282
-Did you do that on purpose?
-You wanted to drink.

1362
01:01:47,203 --> 01:01:49,706
JUN-SEUNG

1363
01:01:49,789 --> 01:01:50,998
"The Room of Truth."

1364
01:01:51,874 --> 01:01:54,502
"Ask one question
to the person of your choice."

1365
01:01:55,086 --> 01:01:57,547
I'd like to ask Si-hyun a question.

1366
01:01:57,630 --> 01:01:59,048
How was your date today?

1367
01:01:59,632 --> 01:02:00,633
It was fun.

1368
01:02:01,134 --> 01:02:03,636
We had good food.

1369
01:02:04,679 --> 01:02:05,847
It was refreshing.

1370
01:02:06,973 --> 01:02:08,141
I could clear my mind.

1371
01:02:08,725 --> 01:02:09,851
You could clear your mind?

1372
01:02:12,311 --> 01:02:13,438
You're up.

1373
01:02:14,105 --> 01:02:15,022
Okay.

1374
01:02:15,106 --> 01:02:16,107
HYUN-JIN

1375
01:02:16,190 --> 01:02:17,316
THE ROOM OF TRUTH

1376
01:02:17,400 --> 01:02:18,735
"The Room of Truth."

1377
01:02:23,114 --> 01:02:25,032
-I pick Ji-young.
-Okay.

1378
01:02:26,451 --> 01:02:28,035
Of everything you've eaten here until now,

1379
01:02:28,870 --> 01:02:30,288
what was the best?

1380
01:02:30,371 --> 01:02:32,123
She's asking if it's <i>hoe</i> or curry.

1381
01:02:32,206 --> 01:02:33,082
They're so different.

1382
01:02:33,166 --> 01:02:34,667
Honestly, isn't <i>hoe</i> better?

1383
01:02:34,751 --> 01:02:36,043
-<i>Hoe</i> or curry.
-Jeez.

1384
01:02:36,127 --> 01:02:37,420
Be honest.

1385
01:02:37,503 --> 01:02:41,466
They ate a whole lot of <i>hoe</i>
and barely touched the curry.

1386
01:02:42,133 --> 01:02:44,051
Do you know what else is annoying?

1387
01:02:44,135 --> 01:02:45,803
Dummies like me

1388
01:02:45,887 --> 01:02:48,639
-You'd pick the yummiest one?
-would really pick what I found yummy.

1389
01:02:49,223 --> 01:02:50,808
Of everything you've eaten here until now,

1390
01:02:51,601 --> 01:02:53,060
what was the best?

1391
01:02:53,644 --> 01:02:55,229
-Of everything I ate here?
-Yeah.

1392
01:03:01,736 --> 01:03:02,737
<i>Hoe</i>.

1393
01:03:09,202 --> 01:03:11,704
SI-HYUN

1394
01:03:15,500 --> 01:03:17,585
"Ask one question to the person
of your choice."

1395
01:03:18,961 --> 01:03:19,962
I pick Ji-young.

1396
01:03:21,631 --> 01:03:24,008
If you had one date pass,

1397
01:03:24,801 --> 01:03:26,511
who would you go on a date with?

1398
01:03:29,305 --> 01:03:30,181
I pick you.

1399
01:03:37,939 --> 01:03:41,609
JI-YOUNG

1400
01:03:41,692 --> 01:03:46,447
"Name the moment
that gave you the most butterflies here."

1401
01:03:54,455 --> 01:03:55,873
At the <i>hoe</i> restaurant,

1402
01:03:55,957 --> 01:03:57,750
when Si-hyun and I

1403
01:03:58,876 --> 01:04:01,254
fed each other <i>hoe</i> lettuce wraps.

1404
01:04:02,588 --> 01:04:03,506
She said that

1405
01:04:05,216 --> 01:04:07,176
-on purpose.
-Of course she did.

1406
01:04:07,260 --> 01:04:08,219
But you know what?

1407
01:04:09,178 --> 01:04:11,347
The person who's most shocked is Si-hyun.

1408
01:04:11,430 --> 01:04:13,516
He was probably so surprised.
"She just shared that?"

1409
01:04:14,016 --> 01:04:15,935
He probably wanted to hide that.

1410
01:04:16,018 --> 01:04:17,061
Of course he did.

1411
01:04:17,144 --> 01:04:18,354
Because he has his options open.

1412
01:04:18,437 --> 01:04:20,189
He was shocked. Si-hyun would have--

1413
01:04:20,273 --> 01:04:22,567
-"Why did you say that?"
-"Why did you say that?"

1414
01:04:22,650 --> 01:04:24,819
"Wasn't that a secret between you and me?"

1415
01:04:24,902 --> 01:04:26,028
But it is entertaining.

1416
01:04:28,865 --> 01:04:30,283
At the <i>hoe</i> restaurant,

1417
01:04:30,366 --> 01:04:32,159
when Si-hyun and I

1418
01:04:33,286 --> 01:04:35,663
fed each other raw fish lettuce wraps.

1419
01:04:41,669 --> 01:04:43,504
Oh my gosh!

1420
01:04:44,547 --> 01:04:46,716
-He shut his eyes tightly.
-He shut them tightly.

1421
01:04:47,300 --> 01:04:48,759
"Jeez, why did you say that?"

1422
01:04:48,843 --> 01:04:51,012
-"Man, I'm in trouble."
-Yeah.

1423
01:04:54,307 --> 01:04:55,641
This is so fun!

1424
01:05:00,605 --> 01:05:01,564
It's me.

1425
01:05:02,732 --> 01:05:06,110
JUN-SEUNG

1426
01:05:06,193 --> 01:05:08,863
"Feed a snack
to someone you're interested in."

1427
01:05:12,283 --> 01:05:13,701
What would be good?

1428
01:05:16,913 --> 01:05:18,247
Have this one.

1429
01:05:24,712 --> 01:05:26,130
-Ji-young.
-Oh, it's me.

1430
01:05:28,341 --> 01:05:29,175
Hyun-jin.

1431
01:05:35,848 --> 01:05:36,933
Wasn't that like a movie scene?

1432
01:05:37,016 --> 01:05:38,434
That was like a scene

1433
01:05:38,517 --> 01:05:39,769
from <i>Reply 1997.</i>

1434
01:05:39,852 --> 01:05:41,812
"Friend? Whatever." It's that line.

1435
01:05:42,939 --> 01:05:45,775
-He was like Seo In-guk.
-He was Seo In-guk.

1436
01:05:45,858 --> 01:05:46,817
Wow.

1437
01:05:46,901 --> 01:05:47,944
That was cool.

1438
01:05:48,027 --> 01:05:49,236
I'd get crazy butterflies.

1439
01:05:49,320 --> 01:05:53,115
<i>Have you made your final decision?</i>

1440
01:05:53,199 --> 01:05:56,160
<i>I feel like a wavering reed</i>
<i>in a field of reeds.</i>

1441
01:05:56,243 --> 01:05:59,789
<i>I had to see it with my own eyes</i>
<i>and hear it with my ears.</i>

1442
01:05:59,872 --> 01:06:01,040
It was hard.

1443
01:06:01,123 --> 01:06:04,710
Hyun-jin, if I asked you right now,
would you be my girlfriend?

1444
01:06:04,794 --> 01:06:07,588
<i>It wasn't just us that had a good time</i>
<i>during those six hours?</i>

1445
01:06:07,672 --> 01:06:09,298
<i>-Did you expect it?</i>
<i>-I regretted it.</i>

1446
01:06:09,382 --> 01:06:11,342
Is it okay to feel regret?

1447
01:06:11,425 --> 01:06:13,469
How would it have been
if I hadn't gone for Ji-young?

1448
01:06:13,552 --> 01:06:14,720
If you hadn't gone for her?

1449
01:06:14,804 --> 01:06:16,263
I was hiding my feelings.

1450
01:06:16,764 --> 01:06:18,099
<i>I kept thinking about Hyun-jin.</i>

1451
01:06:18,182 --> 01:06:19,475
<i>It's the end, but I still don't know.</i>

1452
01:06:19,558 --> 01:06:21,185
<i>It can't be me.</i>

1453
01:06:24,939 --> 01:06:26,941
Subtitle translation by:

1454
01:06:27,024 --> 01:06:28,943
THE LOVE LAB
